info.abstract:
[Behaviour]
Applies an operation between the values of input measures in the same position.

[Parameters]
- input measure type : Ophidia typing. Supported types are a list of:
					'oph_double';
					'oph_float';
					'oph_long';
					'oph_int';
					'oph_short';
					'oph_byte'.
- output measure type : Ophidia typing. Supported types are:
					'oph_double';
					'oph_float';
					'oph_long';
					'oph_int';
					'oph_short';
					'oph_byte'.
- measure a : first input measure.
- measure b : second input measure.
- operation name : type of operation
                    -- 'oph_sum' : compute the sum of the elements;
                    -- 'oph_avg' : compute the average of the elements;
                    -- 'oph_mul' : compute the product of the elements;
                    -- 'oph_max' : compute the maximum of the elements;
                    -- 'oph_min' : compute the minimum of the elements;
                    -- 'oph_arg_max' : return the index of the maximum of the elements;
                    -- 'oph_arg_min' : return the index of the minimum of the elements.
- missingvalue : value to be considered as missing value (set it to NULL if not given);
                 by default it is NAN (for 'oph_double' and 'oph_float').

[Return type]
Binary-array.

[Examples]
oph_operator_array('OPH_DOUBLE|OPH_DOUBLE','OPH_DOUBLE',measure_a,measure_b,'OPH_MAX',NULL)
